X-WR-CALNAME:Bluegrass in La Roche 2026 — Concerts
X-WR-TIMEZONE:Europe/Paris
X-WR-CALDESC:Main Stage\, Day Stage and Street Festival concerts. Bluegrass in La Roche 2026\, La Roche-sur-Foron\, France. 29 July - 2 August 2026.
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-001@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T173000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Workshop Students & Teachers — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Teaching camp students take the main stage to close the 3-day residential camp. Instructors: Kristy Cox (songwriting)\, Jason Bailey (mandolin)\, Carter Lester (banjo)\, Ellie Hakanson (fiddle)\, Tyler Griffith (bass)\, Ondra Kozák (guitar)\, Raphael Maillet (fiddle)\, Patrick Peillon (guitar)\, Dorian Ricaux (mandolin)\, Thierry Loyer (dobro)\, Christian Labonne (banjo)\, Marie Clemence (mandolin/guitar beginners)\, Gilles Rézard (banjo beginners/camp leader)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-002@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T200000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T204500
SUMMARY:🎸 Piotr Bułas & Garage Folks — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Warsaw-based bluegrass band blending authentic American bluegrass with Polish spirit and passion. At the heart of the band is Piotr Bułas - not only a skilled musician but a leading figure on the Polish bluegrass scene whose workshop\, Bułas Banjos\, produces high-quality banjos\, mandolins and guitars played by musicians across Europe and the USA. The band name comes from Piotr's garage where they first got together. Previously played major Polish festivals including Mrągowo\, Wolsztyn and Lesko Country Festivals\, and Nääsville in Sweden. Spotted at EBMA 2025 in Prague\, they play traditional bluegrass\, contemporary covers and original songs with tight vocal harmonies and a nice touch of humour. Album: Memories Fly Away (2025). Members: Piotr Bułas (banjo)\, Weronika Plutecka (fiddle)\, Edward Gorecki (double bass)\, Łukasz Potoczny (mandolin)\, Rafał Jabłoński (guitar)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-003@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T204500
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T211500
SUMMARY:🎸 Opening Ceremony — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-004@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T211500
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T224500
SUMMARY:🎸 Paul & the Alley Cats — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Band formed at Al Ras Bluegrass Festival in Barcelona in 2024. Paul van Vlodrop is a European Bluegrass pioneer with credits including touring with Byron Berline\, Jim Eanes and Chris Jones. Lluís Gómez and Maribel Rivero are well-known La Roche regulars; Jorge Rodriguez Cros played with Flamengrass in 2022. Album: Alley Cat (2023). Members: Paul van Vlodrop (mandolin)\, Lluís Gómez (banjo)\, Maribel Rivero (bass)\, Jorge Rodriguez Cros (guitar)\, Noah Hassler-Forest (fiddle)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-005@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260730T224500
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T000000
SUMMARY:🎸 Kristy Cox Band — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Known as Australia's Queen of Bluegrass\, Kristy Cox grew up in South Australia and is now Nashville-based. Multiple Billboard #1 albums; 6x Golden Guitar Award winner (Australia's CMAs); IBMA Momentum Award finalist for Vocalist of the Year. Previously played La Roche in 2014 with European musicians; now back with her Nashville band. Latest album: Let It Burn (2024\, debuted #1 Billboard Bluegrass). Members: Kristy Cox (guitar/vocals)\, Ellie Hakanson (fiddle)\, Jason Bailey (mandolin)\, Carter Lester (banjo)\, Tyler Griffith (bass)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-006@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T180000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T190000
SUMMARY:🎸 Noah Hassler-Forest — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:1st prize winners at the Rotterdam Bluegrass band contest. Jazz and world music-infused Bluegrass with powerful harmonies and virtuoso playing. First spotted at EBMA 2025 in Prague. Noah Hassler-Forest also appears with Paul & the Alley Cats on Thursday. Members: Noah Hassler-Forest (fiddle)\, Thijs Vrolijk (guitar)\, Joshua ten Doornkaat (mandolin)\, Maribel Rivero (bass)\, Lluís Gómez (banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-007@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 No Man's Land — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Pan-European all-female supergroup making their La Roche debut as a full band — the festival is proud to be the first major European festival to introduce them to the world. All members have performed at La Roche individually before. Members: Signe Borch (guitar\, DK)\, Kylie Kay Anderson (mandolin\, US)\, Loes van Schaijk (bass\, NL)\, Simona Uhereková (banjo\, SK)\, Esther Duerinck (fiddle\, BE)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-008@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T200000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T213000
SUMMARY:🎸 The New Aliquot & David Benda — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Ondra Kozák is one of Europe's foremost Bluegrass artists and has won the La Roche band contest 4 times in 3 different bands on 4 different instruments. New Aliquot came 2nd in 2019 on their only prior appearance. Since then they have toured all over Europe and released 2 albums; collaborating with banjo player David Benda (Milkeaters\, La Roche 2022) since last year. Headlined EBMA Prague in March 2026 — their 10th anniversary year. Album: Keep Going (2024). Members: Ondra Kozák (guitar/fiddle)\, Pavel Tim Duda (bass/guitar)\, Vít Hanulík (mandolin/guitar)\, Karel Začal (dobro)\, David Benda (banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-009@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T213000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T230000
SUMMARY:🎸 The Sentimental Gentlemen — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Part of the buzzing East Nashville Bluegrass community; currently Sierra Ferrell's touring band. The core members (Josh\, Oliver and Geoff) have backed top artists on world tours. Jacob Groopman previously played La Roche with Front Country in 2015. Members: Joshua Rilko (mandolin)\, Oliver Bates Craven (fiddle)\, Geoff Saunders (bass)\, Jacob Groopman (guitar)\, George Guthrie (banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-010@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260731T230000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T000000
SUMMARY:🎸 Veranda — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Montreal-based band with the distinction of playing Bluegrass in both English and French. Captivated the festival at IBMA WOB in Chattanooga with their eclectic mix of respect for old country roots and love of modern sounds\, delivered with plenty of humour. Album: Veranda (2026). Members: Léandre Joly-Pelletier (mandolin)\, Catherine-Audrey Lachapelle (guitar)\, Jean-Philippe Demers-Lelotte aka Johnny Slapper (bass)\, Kieran Poile (fiddle)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-011@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T180000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T190000
SUMMARY:🎸 Yonder Boys — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Berlin-based international outfit who followed the classic La Roche path: Street Festival → Day Stage → Main Stage. Hard to pin down stylistically but dance in and out of Americana\, Bluegrass and folk with excellent harmonies and standard Bluegrass instrumentation. Album: A Makeshift Family (2025). Members: Jason Serious (guitar)\, David Stewart Ingleton (banjo)\, Tomás Peralta (mandolin/banjo/bass/dobro)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-012@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Sweet Sally — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Young California trio from the CBA stable that produced Molly Tuttle and AJ Lee & Blue Summit. Sophia Sparks won the 2024 Rocky Grass mandolin contest and a 2026 Berklee scholarship; Lucy Khadder is a 3-time Young Arts Award winner and Monterey Jazz Festival performer; Clare O'Grady has a background in percussion\, jazz and law. Already performed at Delfest\, CBA Father's Day and IBMA World of Bluegrass. EP: When the Night Falls (2025). Members: Lucy Khadder (fiddle/guitar)\, Sophia Sparks (mandolin/guitar)\, Clare O'Grady (bass)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-013@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T200000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T213000
SUMMARY:🎸 Country GongBang — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Korean Bluegrass band that has become a sensation on the US circuit since their last La Roche appearance in 2022. IBMA international band grant recipients. Standing ovations from Greyfox to the Grand Ole Opry\, plus a memorable backstage jam with their hero Rhonda Vincent. Sing original compositions in Korean. Albums: We All Need Bluegrass (2025 compilation)\, Unknown Poets (2023). Members: Jongsu Yoon (fiddle)\, Yebin Kim (mandolin)\, Sunjae Won (guitar)\, Ki Ha (bass)\, Hyun Ho (banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-014@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T213000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T230000
SUMMARY:🎸 Shelby Means Band — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Born in Kentucky\, raised in Wyoming\, now based in Charleston SC. One of the foremost bass players in Bluegrass. Former member of Della Mae (La Roche 2019 & 2025) and Molly Tuttle & Golden Highway\, winning 2 Grammy Awards (Best Bluegrass Album 2022 & 2023). Debut solo album (2025) features collaborations with Billy Strings\, Molly Tuttle\, Sam Bush\, Jerry Douglas and Ron Block. Album: Shelby Means (2025). Members: Shelby Means (bass/vocals)\, Joel Timmons (guitar)\, Jacob Means (mandolin)\, Ellie Hakanson (fiddle)\, George Guthrie (banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-015@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T230000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T000000
SUMMARY:🎸 Monogram — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Czech Bluegrass institution with 30 years of history\, the Jahoda brothers at their core throughout. Won the La Roche band contest in 2008 and returned as contest winners the following year. Still at the top of the European Bluegrass tree. First La Roche visit in 10 years. Album: Simple Man (2019). Members: Jaromír Jahoda (banjo)\, Zdeněk Jahoda (mandolin)\, Jindřich Vinkler (guitar)\, Erik Banič (bass)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-016@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T180000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T190000
SUMMARY:🎸 William Jack — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Solo cellist from Australia\, classically trained in Austria. Discovered at Your Roots Are Showing Gig Fair in Belfast in January 2026 where he received a standing ovation — rare for a 30-minute showcase. Cites Chris Thile and Tony Rice as influences; his album title This Old Cello Box is taken indirectly from Church Street Blues. Spans Bluegrass\, jazz and classical music on a single instrument. Albums: This Old Cello Box vols 1\, 2 & 3 (2022\, 2024\, 2026). Members: William Jack (cello)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-017@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Blue Lass — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:UK band following the classic La Roche path: Street Festival → Day Stage (Young Talent 2024) → Main Stage 2026. Mix of Bluegrass with Old Time and Folk in both original songs and covers\, reflecting a broad range of influences beyond acoustic music. EP: Skyline and Coalmines (2024). Members: Abbey Thomas (mandolin)\, Holly Wheeldon (fiddle/guitar)\, Ruth Eliza (clawhammer banjo)\, Esther Duerinck (fiddle)\, Noémie Charmetant (bass)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-018@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T200000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T211500
SUMMARY:🎸 Gadan — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Celtic-Americana fusion band that blew away the festival organisers at Your Roots Are Showing in January 2025. Features banjo legend Enda Scahill (We Banjo Three) and Appalachian clawhammer banjoist Eric Long — three banjo players in total alongside mandolin\, fiddle and guitar. Extensive US touring; booked for the Sunday evening 'nearly but not quite Bluegrass' session. Album: May the Divil Tune Your Banjos (2025). Members: Jacob Ventura (guitar/bass)\, Lorenzo Testa (tenor banjo/mandolin)\, Joan Gatti (fiddle)\, Enda Scahill (tenor banjo)\, Eric Long (clawhammer banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-019@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T211500
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T223000
SUMMARY:🎸 Hayde Bluegrass Orchestra — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Oslo-based 7-piece band inspired by the Belgian film The Broken Circle Breakdown. Their Wayfaring Stranger recording has over 20 million YouTube views. Debut album Migrants (2021) debuted at #4 Billboard Bluegrass; follow-up The Broken Circle Sessions (2023) reached #9. Won IBMA Momentum Vocalist of the Year 2022 (Rebekka Nilsson); nominated Band of the Year 2022 & 2023; Norwegian Grammy nominee. Regularly tour the US. Often described as Nickel Creek meets Alison Krauss. New album due 2026. Members: Rebekka Nilsson (vocals)\, Ole Enggrav (guitar)\, Moa Meinich (fiddle)\, David Buverud (bass)\, Emil Brattested (dobro/mandolin)\, Sjur Marqvardsen (accordion)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-020@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T223000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260803T000000
SUMMARY:🎸 Yellofox — Main Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Dutch Folk-Americana band discovered at Your Roots Are Showing in Belfast. Inspired by Paul Simon\, Gram Parsons\, Nick Drake\, Eels and Fleet Foxes — a bluesy\, soulful sound with rich harmonies\, acoustic grooves and honest storytelling. A perfect festival closer. EP: Dream On (2025); Album: For the Dreamers (2023); new album due later 2026. Members: Jorieke de Vet (cello)\, Ronald de Jong (bass)\, Marc Mosmans (acoustic guitar)\, Pauline de Vet (fiddle)\, Roger Verbeek (drums)\, Frans Pruis (lead guitar)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-021@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T120000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T130000
SUMMARY:🎸 Kids on Bluegrass Europe — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Organised by Ti'Pierre Chalfoun and the Jam Hall Association. Brings kids aged 6-16 from across Europe together for two mornings to learn Bluegrass together and communicate through music. 2026 Instructors: Ti'Pierre Chalfoun\, Thomas Marinello\, Marie Scheid
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-022@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T130000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T140000
SUMMARY:🎸 Kristy Cox Band — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:After teaching at the camp and headlining Thursday night\, Kristy and her band return for a final performance. Australia's Queen of Bluegrass; multiple Billboard #1 albums. Members: Kristy Cox (guitar/vocals)\, Ellie Hakanson (fiddle)\, Jason Bailey (mandolin)\, Carter Lester (banjo)\, Tyler Griffith (bass)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-023@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T140000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T150000
SUMMARY:🎸 That's All Folk — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Almost local to La Roche\, from the Tarentaise region of the Alps. First appeared at the Street Festival in 2023 where their dynamic and joyous traditional Bluegrass and pop covers won the audience over. Festival favourite Dorian Ricaux joins them on mandolin. Members: Adrien Garlin (guitar)\, Laurent Chicoisne (banjo/guitar)\, Dorian Ricaux (mandolin)\, Michael Clement (bass)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-024@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T150000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T160000
SUMMARY:🎸 The Sentimental Gentlemen — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Sierra Ferrell's touring band; also on Main Stage Friday evening. Top Nashville session musicians blending traditional and contemporary Bluegrass. Members: Joshua Rilko (mandolin)\, Oliver Bates Craven (fiddle)\, Geoff Saunders (bass)\, Jacob Groopman (guitar)\, George Guthrie (banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-025@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T160000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260801T170000
SUMMARY:🎸 Tim O'Connor Trio — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Irishman living locally in Aix-les-Bains; prolific singer-songwriter and 21st century troubadour. Previously played La Roche in 2009. Music crosses folk\, Irish\, blues and rock effortlessly. Albums: À Mery Cama (2026)\, Manchester St Salford Sky (2025). Members: Tim O'Connor (guitar)\, Bertrand Denechaud (dobro)\, Dave Thom (mandolin/guitar)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-026@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T120000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T130000
SUMMARY:🎸 Grace Honeywell & Jeri Foreman — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Jeri Foreman is Australian and has previously played La Roche with The Fountaineers (Scotland). The duo formed in the UK and have toured Scotland\, England and Australia. Twin fiddles and fresh Bluegrass\, country classics and original songs. Album: The Allure of the Honky Tonk (2025). Members: Grace Honeywell (fiddle/guitar)\, Jeri Foreman (fiddle/guitar)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-027@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T130000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T140000
SUMMARY:🎸 Catch the Goat — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Portales brothers have played together for 40 years\, rooted in the Toulouse Bluegrass scene of the 1980s. Their Dawgrass style (after David Grisman) is enriched by folk\, jazz and classical touches. Latest formation adds the warm sound of the cello. Album: Rocky Lands (2025). Members: Patrick Portales (guitar/fiddle)\, Daniel Portales (mandolin/mandocello)\, Hannah Al-Kharusy (cello)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-028@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T140000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T150000
SUMMARY:🎸 Shelby Means Band — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:A completely different set from Saturday's Main Stage show. Grammy-winning bassist and debut solo artist. Members: Shelby Means (bass/vocals)\, Joel Timmons (guitar)\, Jacob Means (mandolin)\, Ellie Hakanson (fiddle)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-029@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T150000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T160000
SUMMARY:🎸 Country GongBang — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Last chance to see this Korean Bluegrass sensation before they fly home. Also on Saturday Main Stage. Members: Jongsu Yoon (fiddle)\, Yebin Kim (mandolin)\, Sunjae Won (guitar)\, Ki Ha (bass)\, Hyun Ho (banjo)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-030@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T160000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260802T170000
SUMMARY:🎸 Sweet Sally — Day Stage | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Also on Saturday Main Stage. Young California trio from the CBA stable. Members: Lucy Khadder (fiddle/guitar)\, Sophia Sparks (mandolin)\, Clare O'Grady (bass)
LOCATION:La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-031@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Watson Bridge — Street Festival | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Acoustic guitar duo from the French Bluegrass scene\, named after Doc Watson. Isabelle Groll and Jean-Paul Delon reinterpret American roots and Americana songwriters (Gillian Welch\, Darrell Scott\, Sarah Jarosz) with close vocal harmonies\, joined here by Dorian Ricaux (mandolin) and Florence Chapuis (bass). Previously played La Roche in 2012 and 2016. Members: Isabelle Groll (guitar/voice)\, Jean-Paul Delon (guitar/voice)\, Dorian Ricaux (mandolin)\, Florence Chapuis (bass) Efsane Kebab terrace\, town centre. FREE.
LOCATION:Efsane Kebab, 40 rue du Silence, 74800 La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-032@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Blue Morning Train — Street Festival | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:French acoustic string band playing traditional American Bluegrass and roots music\, touring extensively across Europe. Members: Philippe Boutet (guitar/lead vocals)\, Joël Amar (fiddle/vocals)\, Hervé Lascaux (banjo/mandolin)\, Isabelle Lascaux (double bass) Noor Jahan terrace\, town centre. FREE.
LOCATION:Noor Jahan, 121 rue Carnot, 74800 La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-033@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Sweet Potato Vine — Street Festival | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:American bluegrass\, old-time and folk band based in Southern France\, central to the Toulouse Folk Society and the Bluegrassoulet collective. Strong vocal harmonies across traditional and modern bluegrass. Debut self-titled album includes Whiskey Down and Grey Cat on a Tennessee Farm. Members: Jake Braunecker\, Léa Desplats (vocals)\, Maël Mesurolle (vocals/fiddle)\, Noémie Charmetant Le Petit Café terrace\, town centre. FREE.
LOCATION:Le Petit Café, 31 Rue Carnot, 74800 La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-034@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Karoline & the Free Folks — Street Festival | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Lyon-based Americana/country-bluegrass project led by singer-guitarist Karoline\, drawing on Brandi Carlile\, Trey Hensley and the Allman Brothers. Debut album Reckless Dances (2022) was followed by Blooming Haze. Performs as full amplified quartet or in stripped-back acoustic formats. Le Bistro de la Gare terrace\, town centre. FREE.
LOCATION:Le Bistro de la Gare, 1 place de la Gare, 74800 La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-035@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T200000
SUMMARY:🎸 Obejváci — Street Festival | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Rising acoustic band from South Bohemia\, Czech Republic\, blending American-inspired bluegrass and folk with original Czech-language songwriting. Formed in 2021\, taking their name from the living room (obývák) where they first rehearsed. Debut EP Tisíc let (2024) followed by debut album Nebesák. Also showcased at the EBMA European Bluegrass Summit in Prague. Members: Kristýna Barchini (vocals/octave mandolin)\, Luboš Barchini (guitar/vocals)\, Jan Pelech (fiddle/vocals/mandolin)\, Petr Ježek (banjo)\, Štěpán Pavlíček (bass) La Brasserie Rochoise terrace\, town centre. FREE.
LOCATION:La Brasserie Rochoise, 596 Rue du Quarré, 74800 Amancy, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-036@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T193000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T203000
SUMMARY:🎸 Gospel Convicts — Street Festival | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:French Bluegrass Gospel band formed in 2022 by five friends who met at a bluegrass camp\, known for soaring acoustic a cappella harmonies and traditional arrangements of classic gospel and folk hymns\, including Gospel Plow and Swing Low Sweet Chariot. Members: Killian De Bergh (lead vocals/guitar/banjo)\, Serge Aldinger (low baritone)\, Émilie Moretti (soprano)\, Marie Scheid (tenor)\, Mickaël Guérin (baritone) Le Café de la Poste / La Gavroche terrace\, town centre. FREE.
LOCATION:Le Café de la Poste, 10 rue Jean Jaurès, 74800 La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blr2026-037@larochebluegrass2026
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T200000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20260729T210000
SUMMARY:🎸 Blame the Monkey — Street Festival | Bluegrass in La Roche 2026
DESCRIPTION:Italian acoustic country-bluegrass duo formed by Alejandra Del Castillo and Silvio Ferretti\, both on vocals\, banjo and guitar. Sets cover old and new country music\, from Carter Family standards to Guy Clark and 1980s new country. The band's name nods to a playful theory that mistakes can be blamed on the chaotic 'monkeys' regulating the mind. Members: Alejandra Del Castillo (vocals/banjo/guitar)\, Silvio Ferretti (vocals/guitar/banjo) L'Alliance terrace\, town centre. FREE.
LOCATION:L'Alliance, 49 Pl. de la République, 74800 La Roche-sur-Foron, France
END:VEVENT
